  Site navigation sidebar. The top bucket is spec-level (titleless): docs about
  Stisla the framework regardless of implementation. After that, groups cover
  the vanilla implementation: get-started / layout / forms / components /
  overlays (the component buckets are alphabetical). Every entry is a real
  link; unbuilt pages 404 for now and become live as their templates land.

  Optional components (not in the vanilla core bundle — see SPEC.md §10) get
  a muted "Optional" indicator inline. The grouping reflects component family,
  not bundle tier.

  The current page is highlighted at runtime in site.js (compares each link's
  pathname to location.pathname), so we don't need to pass a page key in.
#}
